cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MA. 

This paper focuses on analyzing the consistency between the declared SDK versions and their app API calls in Android apps, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. It also involves parsing Android documents and analyzing app binaries, which could be categorized as programming languages (cs.PL) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses potential remote code execution vulnerabilities, which could be classified as systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA) since machine learning techniques can be used to detect such vulnerabilities.
